The paper deals with joint source-channel coding of compressed sensing measurements using vector quantization. This involves designing an optimal encoder-decoder pair for a vector quantizer to minimize the end-to-end mean square error. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with signal processing and optimization, which are relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as vector quantization, which are relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image and video compression, which are relevant to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
